vec_cons:
theorem antitone.vec_cons (hf : antitone f) (ha : f 0 ≤ a) : antitone (vec_cons a f) :=
  antitone_vec_cons.2 ⟨ha, hf⟩
#align antitone.vec_cons antitone.vec_cons
strict_mono_vec_cons:
@[simp]
theorem strict_mono_vec_cons : strict_mono (vec_cons a f) ↔ a < f 0 ∧ strict_mono f :=
  lift_fun_vec_cons (· < ·)
#align strict_mono_vec_cons strict_mono_vec_cons
strict_anti_vec_cons:
@[simp]
theorem strict_anti_vec_cons : strict_anti (vec_cons a f) ↔ f 0 < a ∧ strict_anti f :=
  lift_fun_vec_cons (· > ·)
#align strict_anti_vec_cons strict_anti_vec_cons
monotone_vec_cons:
@[simp]
theorem monotone_vec_cons : monotone (vec_cons a f) ↔ a ≤ f 0 ∧ monotone f := by
  simpa only [monotone_iff_forall_lt] using @lift_fun_vec_cons α n (· ≤ ·) _ f a
#align monotone_vec_cons monotone_vec_cons

theorem lift_fun_vec_cons {n : ℕ} (r : α → α → Prop) [is_trans α r] {f : fin (n + 1) → α} {a : α} :
    («expr ⇒ » (· < ·) r) (vec_cons a f) (vec_cons a f) ↔ r a (f 0) ∧ («expr ⇒ » (· < ·) r) f f := by
  simp only [lift_fun_iff_succ r, forall_fin_succ, cons_val_succ, cons_val_zero, ← succ_cast_succ, cast_succ_zero]
